oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Southern States and Lime Corporation grounds
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the Southern States and Lime Corporation grounds, including kilns, buildings, and tracks. Three unidentified workers stand at the fork of the tracks, and three others can be seen behind them on the right side. I-40 was later built in the background area of this photo.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Mining; Men; Mine railroads; Mine buildings
